original: Edström, Nils Erik Emanuel, komminister, Stegeborg, f. 3/3/06 i Hauri-da, Jönköp. 1. — Stud:ex. i Linköp. 27, teol. fil. ex. 31, teol. kand., prakt, teol. prov o. prästv. f. Linköp. stift 38. Past:adj. i Kristdala 38, kommin. i Skällvik sed. 44.
translated: Edström, Nils Erik Emanuel, a clergyman, was born on March 3, 1906 in Hauri-da, Jönköping. He passed his studentexamen (final exam of Swedish secondary school) in Linköping in 1927, theological bachelor's degree in 1931, theological candidate's degree, practical theological exam and priestly ordination from Linköping diocese in 1938. He served as a deputy pastor in Kristdala in 1938 and a vicar in Skällvik since 1944.

hasOccupation.description: Served as a deputy pastor in Kristdala from 1938 to 1944
